6 SECTION 4. Arkansas Code § 14-15-805(3)(C), concerning the duties of a
7 county treasurer, is amended to read as follows:
8 (C) The treasurer shall refuse payment of any warrant or
9 check that would cause a deficit balance of the general fund in aggregate.
10
11 SECTION 5. Arkansas Code § 14-15-806 is amended to read as follows:
12 14-15-806. Neglect or refusal to pay warrant check.
13 (a) If any county treasurer shall neglect or refuse to pay any warrant
14 or check drawn on him or her by order of the county court of his or her
15 county, having cash available in the fund on which the warrant or check is
16 drawn, he or she shall forfeit and pay to the holder of the warrant claimant
17 four (4) times the amount thereof.
18 (b) The forfeiture may be recovered by a civil action in the name of
19 the party aggrieved against the treasurer and his or her securities, and the
20 treasurer shall be deemed guilty of a misdemeanor in office and upon
21 conviction shall be removed from office.
22
23 SECTION 6. Arkansas Code § 14-15-809 is amended to read as follows:
24 14-15-809. Resignation, removal, or death.
25 If he or she resigns, is removed from office, or dies, a county
26 treasurer, or his or her executor or administrator, shall immediately make
27 his or her settlement and deliver to his or her successor in office all
28 things pertaining to the office, together with all the moneys monetary funds
29 belonging to the county.
30
